{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f89222cc-64fb-4aae-8650-ca8012ec2a9b","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 (the `MSTest` meta-package 3.x) **drops support for older target frameworks**. Specifically:\n\n| Target Framework | MSTest v3 Support |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ❌ Requires .NET Framework **4.7.2+** |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Requires **.NET 6.0+** |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Requires **.NET 6.0+** |\n\n**What you need to do:**\n\n1. **Update `TargetFrameworks`** — all three of your current targets are unsupported in MSTest v3. You'd need at minimum something like `net8.0;net472` (or `net6.0`/`net9.0` depending on your needs).\n\n2. **Replace the two package references** (`MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter`) with the single unified **`MSTest`** meta-package (version `3.x`).\n\n3. **Review breaking API changes** — MSTest v3 removed some deprecated APIs (e.g., `Assert.That` pattern changes, `DeploymentItem` behavior changes, and some attribute defaults differ).\n\nWould you like me to update the `.csproj` to target compatible frameworks and migrate to MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"80a2c6d8-6c98-4ddc-83a8-fe10cba68417","outputTokens":329,"requestId":"1BD6:32F277:A4285E:BA459B:6A03ECD7"},"id":"dd2eecd1-14f6-4d54-8609-44ebd3133624","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:15:44.382Z","parentId":"ed4035e5-2aff-4716-9aa2-61b055575b5f"}
